{
  "stem": "23090.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was Auschwitz about four to five weeks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and you know, I always tell people, I always tell friends, people, I've given some-- I was invited to make some-- to talk about my experiences in some schools and so on.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, you know, I said, if there's only one way I can tell you what I lived through, or someone like myself, a prisoner of war in Vietnam, or prisoners, people who, who have had some similar experience, is if I could somehow take you on a tour for one minute in Auschwitz, just for one minute.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you would hear the screams, the smell, the stench of, of, of of, human flesh, the exhibition of human beings to other human beings, and the exhibition of human beings dying under conditions that are from, are from one degree to another, from, from, any, any way and level of-- then that's all you would need to understand what the war, and what genocide, and what extermination is all about.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Just one minute.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If there was just one a minute-- and I'm sure that the, the, the captive soldier in Viet Nam and the conditions of the way they were treated, if they could see-- if I could just take one moment to that camp, and the way it was, it would explain everything.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Unfortunately we can't do that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And fortunately, thank God, we don't have to.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But that's what Auschwitz was to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It is my worst nightmare, since I lost my mother, since I lost my sister, since that was my introduction to being alone.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When I say alone, alone doesn't necessarily, you know, mean that are with anybody, that you're alone.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
